# =============================================================================
# lista ↦ cursor — wrap list as a lazy cursor
# =============================================================================
#
# What this example teaches:
#   • lista ↦ cursor — wrap an existing list for cursor-based iteration
#   • Eager buffer wrap — the underlying list is buffered in memory
#
# Syntaxes used:
#   • ↦ (conversion operator) — line 9
#   • incipit (entry point) — line 8
#
# Alternate approaches (not shown):
#   • itera ex lista — direct iteration without cursor wrapping; prefer for simple loops

# Anti-patterns (avoid these):
#   • Building a cursor from an empty list — empty cursors are valid but yield nothing
#   • lista ∷ cursor — static ascription does not create a cursor; use ↦

# Pitfalls:
#   • The underlying list is shared — mutating the original list affects the cursor
#   • Cursor wraps eagerly; large lists still occupy memory

# Learning path:
#   Before: see lista/ exempla (Stage 3) and cursor/ exempla (Stage 6)
#   After:  see cat/src/main.fab (cursor-based patterns for file reading)

# Stage: Phase-1 model, both backends
# Backend: Rust ✓, wasm-text ✓
# =============================================================================
incipit {
    fixum _ r ← [1, 2, 3] ↦ cursor<numerus>
}
